Avoid to lock in a certain Vender (Cloud)

IaaS - infrastructure (physical + network )
PaaS - platform:
    rent enviorment, you code solution
SaaS - software (out the box)
    software runs on the cloud and you use it via the internet
FaaS - function
    write a function, set up triggers
    when the trigger hits the cloud provider runs the function for you

** Advantages **
- cost efficiency
    - No need to maintain expensive hardware
    - pay for what you use
    - less CapEx more OpEx
- accessibility
- faster global Deployment
- less reponsobility 
    - less maintainance 
    - security (physical)
- collaboration
    - easier to experiment, test etc.

## Disadvantages
- lack of control
- requires expertise
- can tax bandwidth
- different security concerns/points of attack
- must be managed properly to not lead to spiralling costs
- vendor lock in
- compliance issues
- service outages

